text: Gustave Rheingans (September 8, 1890 - February 28, 1951) was an American politician and farmer. Born in the Town of Eagle Point, Chippewa County, Wisconsin, Rheingans grew up on a farm. In 1920, he moved to Chippewa Falls, Wisconsin and worked for Farmers Produce Company and was in dairy and truck farming. He also worked as a clerk in a hardware store. Rheingans served in the Wisconsin State Assembly and was a Republican. He also served as sergeant at arms in the 1931, 1935, and 1937 Wisconsin Legislatures. Rheingans died in Chippewa Falls, Wisconsin.'Wisconsin Blue Book 1929,' Biographical Sketch of Gustave Rheingans, pg. 542'Rheingans Dies,' Madison Capitol Times, March 2, 1951, pg. 4 ==Notes== Category:1890 births Category:1951 deaths Category:People from Chippewa County, Wisconsin Category:Farmers from Wisconsin Category:Wisconsin Republicans Category:Employees of the Wisconsin Legislature Category:Members of the Wisconsin State Assembly Category:20th- century American politicians
